node.text: Dee Snider, former lead singer of Twisted Sister, made an emotional piano version of 'We're Not Gonna Take It' to help fundraise for the campaign to help children with cancer in the United States.  Listen and try not to get emotional with this beautiful version of the band's greatest classic! 😎🤘❤ 🇺🇸🇧🇷Dee Snider, ex vocalista do Twisted Sister, fez uma emocionante versão em piano para 'We're Not Gonna Take It' para ajudar na arrecadação de fundos para a campanha de ajuda às crianças com câncer nos Estados Unidos. Escute e tente não se emocionar com esta bela versão do maior clássico da banda! 😎🤘❤

node.text:
When my son learned to write in Portuguese the first thing he wrote was a letter to his mom.. It end up like this.. “ Mom thank God I look like you, imagine if I was my fathers face 🤣🤣 I have to agree with him 🤷🏻‍♂️🤷🏻‍♂️🤣 God is a fair soul 🤷🏻‍♂️🤷🏻‍♂️🤷🏻‍♂️🤣🤣🤣❤️
🇺🇸🇺🇸🇧🇷🇧🇷 Quando meu filho aprendeu a escrever em português a primeira coisa que ele escreveu foi uma carta para a mãe dele .. Terminava assim .. “Mãe graças a Deus eu me pareço com você, imagina se eu fosse a cara do meu pai 🤣🤣
 Não posso mentir concordo com ele 🤣🤣🤣 Deus é justo 🤷🏻‍♂️🤷🏻‍♂️🤣

node.text:
Me and my brother @josealfredopadilha were arguing about a technique. So we ended the discussion right there. So there is no right place and time to pass on our knowledge. Jiu-jitsu is present 24 hours in our lives, it is our essence, our soul, our personality.  We have jiu-jitsu in our veins and we go anywhere and train anywhere with a self-confidence that non-practitioners of the gentle art will never understand.  Be on the floor of a restaurant or on the mat, fodacy we are jiu-jitsu.
.
🇧🇷 🇺🇲 🇧🇷 🇺🇲 🇧🇷 🇺🇲 🇧🇷 🇺🇲 🇧🇷 🇺🇲 🇧🇷 🇺🇲
.
Eu e meu irmão @josealfredopadilha estávamos discutindo sobre uma posição. Então acabamos com a discussão ali mesmo pra não acabar a amizade. Não existe lugar e hora certa para passar nosso conhecimento a diante. O jiu-jitsu está presente 24h da nossa vida, é nossa essência, nossa alma, nossa personalidade. Nós que temos jiu-jitsu em nossas veias entramos em qualquer lugar e treinamos em qualquer lugar com uma segurança que os não praticantes da arte nunca irão entender. Seja no chão de um restaurante ou no tatame, fodacy nós somos jiu-jitsu.

#repost @adrianolima_bjj
. 
Medals are made out of sweat, blood, tears and fighting in the gym every day. As the poet @renzograciebjj used to say, fighting is the best thing a man can have in his soul. 
. 
🇧🇷🇺🇲🇧🇷🇺🇲🇧🇷🇺🇲🇧🇷🇺🇲🇧🇷🇺🇲🇧🇷🇺🇲
. 
Medalhas são feitas de suor, sangue, lágrimas e porrada todos os dias. Sábias são as palavras do poeta @renzograciebjj
A luta é a melhor coisa que um homem pode ter em sua alma. 
. 
#black #belt #self #defense #brazilian #jiujitsu #bjj #inspiration #motivation #lifestyle #medal #abudhabi #dubai #Coach #uaejjf

Bill Wallace is an American martial artist who was a Professional Karate Association (PKA) world Middleweight full-contact karate champion for six years. Wallace administers an organization of karate schools under his "Superfoot" system. He was elected to Black Belt Magazine's Hall of Fame in 1973 as "Tournament Karate Fighter of the Year" and again in 1978 as "Man of the Year."[10] His film credits include A Force of One with Chuck Norris; Killpoint, with Cameron Mitchell; Continental Divide and Neighbors, with John Belushi; The Protector, with Jackie Chan; Los Bravos with Hector Echavarria; A Prayer for the Dying, with Mickey Rourke; Ninja Turf; and Sword of Heaven. 
This amazing soul has inspired generations of future fighters, me among them.. I would wait anxious to our Black Belt Magazine that would arrive in Brazil with a delay of around four months, every time I could hold a copy I would look up my heros, and “SUGARFOOT” like I always called him, I just couldn’t say Superfoot would get lost in my head’s translation for some crazy reason, was always a STAR to my soul.. Life gave me the gift of meeting him and allowed me to be his friend.. His simplicity, his humor, his amazing personality makes him ten times greater than all the great things I could imagine he could be. I’m his humble fan for life.
THANK YOU BILL SUGARFOOT WALLACE FOR BEING YOU…. OUR HERO
.
.
.
.
.
